&lt;h1&gt;Highly Specialist Clinical or Counselling Psychologist, Band 8A&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Community Mental Health Directorate (Greenwich)Psychological Therapies - Adult Mental Health&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The post is full-time and is fixed for one year to cover maternity leave.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a psychologist to make a major contribution to the Greenwich (ADAPT) community psychological therapies service. We wish to recruit an accomplished psychologist with a commitment to multidisciplinary team working with adults presenting with severe and enduring mental health difficulties. You will provide comprehensive assessments, manage referrals, offer individual and group treatment and have proven skills and experience of working in secondary care Adult Mental Health. This post would suit an experienced band 7 looking for career development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Greenwich has 10 psychological therapists working across ADAPT (Anxiety Depression and Personality disorder and Trauma). You will be with based within the Woolwich /Charlton area of Greenwich . We have psychological therapists with extensive training and experience in CBT, MBT, psychodynamic and systemic approaches. Greenwich has a well established IAPT service that liaises with secondary care to provide an integrated service. We have good working relationships with both managers and other senior clinicians, and psychology is well represented in senior managerial and at board level.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that Oxleas operates a probationary period, further information is available on request.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Graham Thomson, 07767 863234, graham.thomson1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
